On a typical weekday in the summer, about how many hours did you generally spend in the mid-day sun (when you were) In your teens?
column9: "Mid-day sun" means those hours when the sun is more than halfway up in the sky. For most of the United States, that would be between the hours of 10 AM and 4PM Daylight Savings Time.
